author: Inside Edition
description: The passing of Hollywood icon Robert Redford is reigniting a tantalizing cold case. Sidney Wells, 22, was engaged to the star's daughter, Shauna. In 1983, he was found shot to death in his apartment in Boulder, Colorado. The only suspect was Well's roommate, Thayne Smika, and he has been on the run for decades. Smika is still on the FBI's most wanted list. Inside Edition spoke to Wells’ brother.
title: Robert Redford's Death Reignites Son-In-Law To-Be's Cold Case

author: Inside Edition
description: Welcome to the high octane premiere of "Dancing with the Stars." Robert Irwin, son of crocodile hunter Steve Irwin, and brother of Bindi Irwin, stole the show Tuesday night. Robert has big shoes to fill. Bindi won the competition 10 years ago. Robert was in the audience back then, at age 10. Bindi was there for her brother Tuesday night. Alec Baldwin's wife, Hilaria, also impressed the judges. The actor was there with their kids in Los Angeles.
title: Robert Irwin Steals The Show At 'Dancing With The Stars' Premiere

author: Inside Edition
description: A New Orleans Saints cheerleader experienced a nightmare. Lily Lowry, 28, went flying across the field after she and two squad members lost their grip. Lowry landed on her side. She is back on her feet and spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall. The stunt the cheerleaders were trying to do was called a "human double dutch." Lowry has been a Saints cheerleader for three years and she says, accidents happen.
title: Stunt Gone Wrong Sends New Orleans Saints Cheerleader Flying

author: Inside Edition
description: Carrie Edwards defied spectacular odds by winning a huge Powerball jackpot. Edwards said she picked her winning numbers by consulting with Chat GPT. She is now giving away $150,000, all the money she won, to charity, including one that is very close to home. Her husband Steve died from dementia in 2023. Steve was a firefighter in Fairfax County, Virginia, and responded to the Pentagon on 9/11. “All he ever wanted to do was help people," Edwards said. Now she's helping people with her jackpot.
title: Woman Uses ChatGPT To Win Powerball Jackpot And Donates All Of It

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump and first lady Melania made their state visit to the UK. Trump and Melania were greeted by Prince William and Princess Catherine on the Windsor Castle grounds then walked across the lawn to meet King Charles and Queen Camilla. Twenty miles away in central London, demonstrators took to the streets. The night before, protestors projected a photo of Trump and Jeffrey Epstein onto the walls of the castle.
title: President Trump And First Lady Melania Greet King Charles

author: Inside Edition
description: A father was eating dinner when suddenly a mozzarella stick lodged in his throat and he started choking. His wife patted him on the back, but it didn’t work. The pregnant wife jumped into action with the Heimlich maneuver but her six-month baby bump was in the way. She turned her belly to the side to save her husband and unborn child. It worked. Inside Edition's Jim Moret spoke to hero mom Samantha Matthews and husband Dan.
title: Pregnant Mom Performs Heimlich Maneuver To Save Husband’s Life

author: Inside Edition
description: First responders rushed to the scene of a house fire in Illinois, hoping to save anyone who might be home. Luckily, there was only one occupant at the time: Oakley, an American Staffordshire Terrier. The good boy didn't make a sound, not even barking when he heard the cops breaking into his house. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Dog Insists On Being Leashed While Rescued From House Fire In Illinois

author: Inside Edition
description: The man charged with murdering Charlie Kirk admitted in a text message to his roommate that he was responsible for the assassination of the conservative activist, according to court documents released by prosecutors.
title: Texts Between Charlie Kirk Suspect And Roommate Revealed #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Diane Wright was walking her Shih Tzu puppy by a creek outside Tampa when an alligator suddenly appeared and lunged for the dog.
title: Florida Woman Punches Gator To Save Puppy #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: The water off Santa Monica is going pink, and it's not because a certain blockbuster film is getting a sequel. The reason is more scientific. UCLA is conducting an experiment on the breakwater that was constructed back in 1934. After nearly a century of harsh weather and storms, researchers fear it is no longer protecting the beach as it originally did. They're using the non-toxic, temporary pink fluorescent dye to track the water's path. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 'Barbie Beach' Project Turns Ocean Pink In Santa Monica For Science Experiment

author: Inside Edition
description: When police in Washington responded to a disturbance call, they found another cop already there. But something didn't seem right.
title: Man Impersonating Cop Caught By Actual Cops #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A New York judge just dropped two terrorism charges against Luigi Mangione, who is accused in the December 2024 killing of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson.
title: Luigi Mangione No Longer Faces Terrorism Charges #shorts
